    <!-- Slide 3: The Birth of Algebra -->
    <div id="slide3" class="slide" data-background="#3b82f6">
        <div class="content-box">
            <h3 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">The Birth of Algebra</h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-white leading-relaxed mb-6">
                His most famous book, <em>Kitāb al-jabr wa al-muqābalah</em>, gave us the word **"algebra."** The book presented a systematic method for solving linear and quadratic equations. It introduced the two core operations of "al-jabr" (completion) and "al-muqābalah" (balancing), which are the basis for manipulating equations today.
            </p>
            <img src="https://placehold.co/400x250/bae6fd/000?text=Page+from+Algebra+Manuscript" alt="A page from an old Arabic algebra manuscript" class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl shadow-lg mt-4 mb-6">
            <a href="https://www.aljazeera.com/video/science-in-a-golden-age/2015/10/20/al-khwarizmi-the-father-of-algebra" target="_blank" class="resource-button inline-block">Watch a video on Algebra's origin</a>
            <div class="mt-8 flex justify-center space-x-4">
